properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 31 at 1:27PM MST until February 2 at 3:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning and Watches across portions of northern and
central Wyoming Tonight through Saturday Night...

.Strong winds aloft and a tight pressure gradient will combine for
high winds across the Cody Foothills and Absaroka Mountains
tonight into Saturday. The strong winds will last across the
Absaroka Mountains through Saturday night. A tight pressure
gradient will also result in strong to possibly high wind across
southeast Fremont into Natrona County Saturday and Saturday night.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona
County Lower Elevations.

* WHEN...From Saturday morning through late Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. A blow over risk for light
and high profile vehicles including camper trailers and semi
trucks.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
